node.text:
So, I hope you find this as funny as I do. This is my bf poking a little fun at those people we’ve all seen on here, pulling cards and talking out of their asses, convincing you to take their courses etc. I guess I’m also sort of a spiritual entrepreneur, but I try to steer clear of telling people that buying my products will do x, y or z for you... Enjoy! Watch out for money hungry lizard people 😬
.
.
.

node.text:
If you love Salem then you need one of these commemorative collector’s coins I designed. One side refers to the past with The Witch House, the last standing structure with ties to the witch trials in 1692 and the other side represents the modern witch community thriving there today.
They come in a black velvet drawstring bag. 
.
.
.
#witchesofinstagram #thewitchhouse #salemmassachusetts #witchart #witchy #witchhouse #historicsalem #fullmoon #witchcraft #salemma #witchyvibes #witchcity #witches #witchcommunity #modernwitch

node.text:
The Tower comes up in Tarot readings when the truth has been exposed, when the sh!t hits the fan and it’s time to rebuild your life. Wear this to show you’re not afraid to face anything that comes your way, that you’re ready to be honest with yourself or to channel the power to change and start fresh.
.
.
.
#tarot #thetower #tarotreadersofig #witchesofinstagram #tarotlove #tarotguidance #tarotcommunity

node.text:
New hypnotic spinning pendant! This was inspired by my great aunt Madeline who would bring a spiral wheel to our house and try to hypnotize us when we were kids.
I find it very relaxing to spin the wheel, kind of like a mediation ring. I had been searching for something like this with no luck so I decided to design one that could be worn. 
.
.
.
#witchesofinstagram #hypnotized #witchythings #witchlife #hypnotic #witchystyle #witching #witches

node.text:
The Angel from The Lovers card encouraging you to Say Yes To Love while The Devil reminds you to Say No To Fear. Carry this coin around as a lucky charm, use it as a deck weight or flip it for decision making…
.
.
.

node.text:
Here’s a little glimpse of some of the stuff I’ve been working on in the pottery studio. I’ve just made some experimental pieces and played around with texture and printing my stamps in the clay. I’m still very new to this, but it’s been fun and a nice break from my usual routine. I can’t wait to see my first batch of stuff come out of the kiln.
.
.
.
#tarotart #thehighpriestess #witchy #tarotcommunity #tarotreadersofig #witchesofinstagram #tarotlovers #tarotaddict #tarotreaders #witch #shiningmoonstudio

node.text:
Tarot, tarot everywhere…
Strength is first since Leo season is upon us. I isolate the imagery from the cards, carve them as stamps and use the prints to design these. Some of the figures needed to be completed beyond the frame of the card to stand alone, like Death’s horse, Temperance’s wings and a couple others.
.
.
.

.

node.text:
Theban is a witches’ code used to conceal and enhance your spellwork. I want to bring it back to modern witchcraft so I designed this set of oracle dice using this magickal alphabet. Roll the dice and look for meaningful words or phrases that come through. Use them with your Tarot cards or for more information after a reading. Some may even dare to use them to communicate with the other side 👻 Check them out on my website✨✨✨
.
.
.

node.text:
Preorder this new Salem themed coin I designed! It should be ready to ship out by the end of the month. The coin features The Witch House on one side, representing the past, and the other side represents the present, with the symbol for modern witchcraft and the phrase “We thrive here now” since Salem has come to be known as Witch City. The first twenty orders will receive a free black acrylic coin stand.
I could use some help spreading the word about this coin since my IG account is slowly dying, so please feel free to repost or put it up as a story. I’d really appreciate it!
.
.
.
